  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN156.1-kilavi">talaimakaḷai <app><lem>yiṭattuyttut</lem><rdg wit="#C3 #C7">yiṭattuyttu vantu</rdg></app> <app><lem>tōḻi</lem><rdg wit="#C3">om.</rdg></app> talaimakaṉai varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante urged HIM for marriage after having sent HER to the [meeting] place.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN156.1">
              <l>muracuṭaic celvar puravi cūṭṭu</l>
              <l>mūṭṭuṟu kavari tūkki yaṉṉa</l>
              <l>ceḻuñcey nelliṉ cēyari <supplied>puṉiṟṟā</supplied>k</l>
              <l>katirmuta <supplied>ṟi</supplied>ṉṟa lañcik kāvalar</l>
              <l>pāka lāykoṭip pakaṉṟaiyoṭu parīik</l>
              <l>kāñciyi ṉakattuk karumparu kiyākkun</l>
              <l>tīmpuṉa <supplied>lū</supplied>ra tiṟava tākak</l>
              <l>kuvaḷai yuṇka ṇivaḷum yāṉuṅ</l>
              <l>kaḻaṉi yāmpaṉ muḻuneṟip paittaḻai</l>
              <l>kāyā ñāyiṟ ṟākat talaippap</l>
              <l>poytal pāṭip polikeṉa vantu</l>
              <l>niṉṉakāp piḻaitta tavaṟō peruma</l>
              <l>kaḻaluṅ kaṇṇiyuṅ kaiyuṟai yāka</l>
              <l>nilaikkōṭṭu veḷḷai nālcevik kaṭāay</l>
              <l>nilaittuṟaik kaṭavuṭ kuḷappaṭa vōccit</l>
              <l>taṇimaruṅ kaṟiyāḷ yā<supplied>a</supplied>y</l>
              <l>maṇimaruṇ mēṉi poṉṉiṟaṅ koḷalē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Oh man from a village of sweet floods, (7ab)</l>
                <l>where the watchmen, afraid that the cow with a new-born [calf] might eat</l>
                <l>from the ears in the red bunches of paddy from the lush field, (3f.)</l>
                <l>as if it was hung with the chowries stitched on (2)</l>
                <l>as a decoration of the horse of drum-possessing rich people, (3)</l>
                <l>tear off selected creepers of Pākal together with jalap (5)</l>
                <l>[and] tie [her] cautiously(?) by the sugarcane among the Portia trees, (6)</l>
                <l>was it for the mistake, o great one, that we went wrong in smiling at you, (12)</l>
                <l>she with waterlily[-like] kajal eyes and me, so that it would be proper (7cd-8)</l>
                <l>coming to say “may it flourish”, singing the Poytal, (11)</l>
                <l>when [you] offered [to us], so that in the sun it would not be [so] hot, (10)</l>
                <l>fresh foliage [and] whole calyxes of white lotus from the field (9)</l>
                <l>that mother who does not know a way to appease [it], (16)</l>
                <l>puts it inwardly down to the god with the ghat as [his] station, (15)</l>
                <l>urging [upon him] the hanging ears of a goat with stately(?) horns, (14)</l>
                <l>with an anklet and a chaplet to be a present, (13)</l>
                <l>takes in the gold colour of [our] sapphire-like body? (17)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
